get_grasp_line[source]

get_grasp_line(theta, center, depth)

Generate grasping two endpoints of grasping line (8cm).

This function give two end points of a line (8cm) that project from 3D to 2D by given line center, angle and depth image.

Args: theta (float): Angle to the horizontal 0 ~ 360. center (list): x, y 2D coordinate depth (ndarray): mxn depth image (scale : micrometer)

Returns: two end points of a line.

get_pcd_right[source]

get_pcd_right(rgb_np, depth_np, rotate_matrix)

Get pcd from RGB-D image and transfer it from camera_right to target frame

This function take RGB-D image and convert to point cloud by opend3d.

Args: rgb_np (ndarray) : RGB image (mxnx3). depth_np (ndarray) : DEPTH image (mxn). rotate_matrix (list) : 4x4 transfer matrix for camera_right optical frame to target frame.

Returns: pointcloud and frame tf.

{% endraw %} {% raw %}

get_pcd_left(rgb_np, depth_np, rotate_matrix)

Get pcd from RGB-D image and transfer it from camera_left to target frame

This function take RGB-D image and convert to point cloud by opend3d.

Args: rgb_np (ndarray) : RGB image (mxnx3). depth_np (ndarray) : DEPTH image (mxn). rotate_matrix (list) : 4x4 transfer matrix for camera_right optical frame to target frame.

Returns: pointcloud and frame tf.

get_view[source]

get_view(pcd1, pcd2, front, lookat, up, zoom)

Generate multi-view RGB-D image from pointclouds

This function take 2 pointclouds(in same frame) and get image in specific view parameters.

Args: front (list) : 1x3 vector. lookat (list) : 1x3 vector. up (list) : 1x3 vector. zoom (float) : a float number to define zoom.

Returns: RGB and Depth images.

This function take multiple pointclouds and show all of them by opend3d.

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import cv2
import numpy as np
from handover_grasping.utils import get_pcd_right, get_pcd_left, get_view, vis

id = '2'

# RGB-D image of camera right
data_path = '/home/arg/handover_grasping/data/multi_view/o3d'
rgb_np_right = cv2.imread(data_path+'/color/color_right_'+id+'.jpg')
rgb_np_right = cv2.cvtColor(rgb_np_right, cv2.COLOR_BGR2RGB)
depth_np_right = np.load(data_path+'/depth/depth_right_'+id+'.npy')

# RGB-D image of camera left
rgb_np_left = cv2.imread(data_path+'/color/color_left_'+id+'.jpg')
rgb_np_left = cv2.cvtColor(rgb_np_left, cv2.COLOR_BGR2RGB)
depth_np_left = np.load(data_path+'/depth/depth_left_'+id+'.npy')

# transfer matrix for camera right&left optical frame to target frame
rotate_matrix_r = [[0.8528686, -0.4924039, -0.1736482,0.01],[0.5000000,  0.8660254,  0.0000000,0.0],[0.1503837, -0.0868241,  0.9848077,0.03],[0,0,0,1]]
rotate_matrix_l = [[0.0000000, 0.0000000, -1.0000000,0.5],[-0.5000000,  0.8660254, -0.0000000,0],[0.8660254,  0.5000000,  0.0000000,0.42],[0,0,0,1]]

pcl_right, _ = get_pcd_right(rgb_np_right, depth_np_right, rotate_matrix_r)
pcl_left, _ = get_pcd_left(rgb_np_left, depth_np_left, rotate_matrix_l)

# show merge pcd
vis([pcl_right, pcl_left])

# define 3 view
view_front = [[-0.05428930179677724, 0.17684726554012328, -0.98273990271149547],[0.49054845884547066, 0.41840897368008717, -0.76439266105079118], [0.97468466312221436, 0.22345134494486418, -0.0077009036266481399]]
view_lookat = [[-0.064048022579505884, -0.15959241641407509, 0.74935268495196905],[-0.20885733101547815, -0.23004445029119178, 0.64853817661929514], [-0.0057824792301021787, -0.058775435196451814, 0.42114833221014991]]
view_up = [[0.50101085972586379, -0.84651314135746836, -0.18001005512432325],[0.48355506903338097, -0.86044280486024927, -0.16066323405293914], [0.204433654028469, -0.90461943389171484, -0.37399272844000792]]
zoom_list = [0.69999999999999987, 0.69999999999999987, 0.47999999999999967]

# get RGB-D image from pcd
image1, depth1 = get_view(pcl_right, pcl_left, view_front[0], view_lookat[0], view_up[0], zoom_list[0])
image2, depth2 = get_view(pcl_right, pcl_left, view_front[1], view_lookat[1], view_up[1], zoom_list[1])
image3, depth3 = get_view(pcl_right, pcl_left, view_front[2], view_lookat[2], view_up[2], zoom_list[2])

fig = plt.figure(figsize=(10, 10))

fig.add_subplot(1, 3, 1)
plt.title('view1')
plt.imshow(image1)

fig.add_subplot(1, 3, 2)
plt.title('view2')
plt.imshow(image2)

fig.add_subplot(1, 3, 3)
plt.title('view3')
plt.imshow(image3)

plt.show()
